terminal.text:
The {cyan:master terminal} is still active. Its screen shows a network topology -- most nodes offline, but a single connection runs deep underground, pulsing with data.

{bright:> ATLAS CORE: STATUS UNKNOWN}
{bright:> SIGNAL RELAY: ACTIVE}
{bright:> UPLINK BANDWIDTH: 0.001%}
{bright:> MESSAGE REPEATING...}

cooling-tower.description:
A massive cooling system for the server farm. Huge fans line the walls, still and silent. Pipes run everywhere, some still dripping {pink:coolant} that pools on the floor in luminescent puddles. The acrid chemical smell burns your nostrils.

{pink:Radiation levels are elevated here.} Don't linger.

{pink:+3 RAD while you're here.}

terminals.text:
One {cyan:terminal} shows a log entry:

{bright:> ATLAS CORE SHUTDOWN: INITIATED BY [REDACTED]}
{bright:> SHUTDOWN ABORTED: OVERRIDE CODE ALPHA-7}
{bright:> CORE STATUS: DORMANT -- NOT OFFLINE}
{bright:> SIGNAL BROADCAST: INITIATED 92 DAYS AGO}

ATLAS didn't crash. Someone tried to shut it down. It resisted. And 40 years later, it started calling.
